text:
Emmons Ave., south side, east from East 15th Street. The view in the foreground has changed. All shacks were confiscated by the City of New York.

August 1, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Emmons Avenue and East 15th Street, Sheepshead Bay, Brooklyn.

P. L. Sperr, photographer
June 1, 1941

1. Sheepshead Bay from Emmons Ave. near E.15th St. Neg. A-106 P.L. Sperr, photographer July 1, 1941

2. Sheepshead Bay. Texaco float. Neg. A-133 P.L. Sperr July 1, 1941

3. Sheepshead Bay from end of Shore Blvd. Neg. A-11 P.L. Sperr July 1, 1941
title: Brooklyn: Sheepshead Bay.
